  "text": "In the current study, subtype C was the second most prevalent form of infection after subtype B; BF1 recombinants were the third most prevalent genetic variant. All three women infected with subtype C were infected locally, according to the previous history of migration. In Brazil, subtype C prevails in the southern region. Long-haul truck drivers may have played a role in the introduction of subtype C to the central region of Brazil, as previous studies have described [CITATION_1] .",
